cs.CL, cs.AI, cs.LG, cs.CV, cs.IR 

Reasoning: 
- cs.CL (Computation and Language) is the most likely category as the paper deals with grounded lexical semantics and natural language processing. 
- cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) is also likely as the paper discusses machine learning models for semantic fitness scoring and composition. 
- cs.LG (Machine Learning) is relevant as the paper explores different classifier types and their underlying mechanics. 
- cs.CV (Computer Vision) is relevant as the paper uses a visual reference resolution task and the refCOCO dataset. 
- cs.IR (Information Retrieval) is relevant as the paper discusses embedding the classifier coefficients and leveraging distributional representations.
